---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  topic="About Brenda"
  description="The artist behind Balloonia Events. Custom balloon installations built in London Ontario for weddings, showers, corporate events, birthdays, and graduations."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'About', url: '/about' },
  ]}
>
  <section class="about-hero section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">The artist</p>
      <h1>The artist behind Balloonia.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Brenda has been building balloon installations long enough to know exactly which jobs are worth taking and which ones to send elsewhere. She takes most of them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-body section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>What the work is meant to do</h2>
      <p>
        An arch that frames the head table like it belonged there. A ceiling install that's still tight at the end of the night. A color palette that reads correctly in the photographer's flash, not just on the order form. Decor that sets the room before guests notice the decor.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's the brief on every install Brenda takes.
      </p>

      <h2>Brenda</h2>
      <p>
        London Ontario. Spanish first, English when she needs it. Full-time at this for years. Trained, mentored, busy. She runs the studio at 412 Newbold St alone, which is how she likes it: one project at a time, with full attention.
      </p>

      <h2>What ends up in her calendar</h2>
      <p>
        Weddings, kids' birthdays, baby and bridal showers, corporate brand events, milestone parties, graduations. The skew is toward weekends and toward installs that have a structural challenge or a color brief that takes more than a quick read.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll see when she's done</h2>
      <p>
        A room that reads the way you'd been picturing it for months. A photograph that ages well. Decor that sits inside the event rather than competing with it. Cleanup handled, no pieces left behind.
      </p>

      <div class="about-cta-wrap">
        <h2>Tell her about your event.</h2>
        <p>
          Date, venue, colors, what you're picturing. Brenda's reply lands within 24 hours, with no commitment.
        </p>
        <div class="about-cta">
          <CTAButton href="/quote" variant="primary" size="lg">Get a quote</CTAButton>
          <CTAButton href="/portfolio" variant="secondary" size="lg">Browse recent installs</CTAButton>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-cta-wrap {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }
  .about-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
  }
</style>
